Street lights [Courtesy]  Naivasha residents have raised the alarm over street lights vandalism.   Most affected are Kabati, Site, Kihoto and Lakeview estates.  Leaders have blamed scrap metal dealers for the continued vandalism. Lake View MCA Simon Wanyoike Wanang said the county had lost millions of shillings due to vandalism. He called for swift arrests, saying it was a racket involving youths and traders.   Naivasha OCPD Samuel Waweru said investigations had started but no arrest had been made.    By Jael Mboga | 4 hours ago By Nikko Tanui | 7 hours ago By Irissheel Shanzu | 7 hours ago By Antony Gitonga | 8 hours ago